Note:
==============================================================================
GRAPHQL - GraphQL AST: Query / Mutation / Subscription + SDL (Tier 1)
==============================================================================

Implements the GraphQL substrate per the GraphQL specification October
2021 edition (https://spec.graphql.org/October2021/), covering:

  - Executable Document (sections 2.2-2.10):
      * Operation definitions (query / mutation / subscription)
      * Field selections, arguments, directives
      * Fragment definitions and fragment spreads
      * Inline fragments with optional type conditions
      * Variable definitions and uses
      * Aliased fields, nested selection sets

  - Schema Definition Language (sections 3.x):
      * Scalar / Object / Interface / Union / Enum / Input Object types
      * List type and Non-Null type wrappers
      * Schema definition (query / mutation / subscription root types)
      * Directive definitions

Record layouts (all 40 bytes):
  off  0  kind tag         GQL_*
  off  8  payload 0        (name string or operand pointer)
  off 16  payload 1        (selection set / args / fields list, etc.)
  off 24  payload 2        (variables list / directives list, etc.)
  off 32  payload 3        (type condition / default value / extra)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: KIND CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Executable document kinds.
Constant GQL_OPERATION as Integer is 1
Constant GQL_SELECTION_SET as Integer is 2
Constant GQL_FIELD as Integer is 3
Constant GQL_ARGUMENT as Integer is 4
Constant GQL_FRAGMENT_DEFINITION as Integer is 5
Constant GQL_FRAGMENT_SPREAD as Integer is 6
Constant GQL_INLINE_FRAGMENT as Integer is 7
Constant GQL_VARIABLE_DEFINITION as Integer is 8
Constant GQL_VARIABLE as Integer is 9
Constant GQL_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 10

Note: Value kinds (used inside arguments, default values).
Constant GQL_VALUE_INT as Integer is 11
Constant GQL_VALUE_FLOAT as Integer is 12
Constant GQL_VALUE_STRING as Integer is 13
Constant GQL_VALUE_BOOLEAN as Integer is 14
Constant GQL_VALUE_NULL as Integer is 15
Constant GQL_VALUE_ENUM as Integer is 16
Constant GQL_VALUE_LIST as Integer is 17
Constant GQL_VALUE_OBJECT as Integer is 18
Constant GQL_VALUE_VARIABLE as Integer is 19

Note: Type system kinds.
Constant GQL_TYPE_NAMED as Integer is 20
Constant GQL_TYPE_LIST as Integer is 21
Constant GQL_TYPE_NON_NULL as Integer is 22
Constant GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_SCALAR as Integer is 23
Constant GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_OBJECT as Integer is 24
Constant GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_INTERFACE as Integer is 25
Constant GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_UNION as Integer is 26
Constant GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_ENUM as Integer is 27
Constant GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_INPUT_OBJECT as Integer is 28
Constant GQL_FIELD_DEFINITION as Integer is 29
Constant GQL_INPUT_VALUE_DEFINITION as Integer is 30
Constant GQL_ENUM_VALUE_DEFINITION as Integer is 31
Constant GQL_SCHEMA_DEFINITION as Integer is 32
Constant GQL_DIRECTIVE_DEFINITION as Integer is 33

Note: Operation types.
Constant GQL_OP_QUERY as Integer is 1
Constant GQL_OP_MUTATION as Integer is 2
Constant GQL_OP_SUBSCRIPTION as Integer is 3

Constant GQL_RECORD_SIZE as Integer is 40
Constant GQL_OFF_KIND as Integer is 0
Constant GQL_OFF_P0 as Integer is 8
Constant GQL_OFF_P1 as Integer is 16
Constant GQL_OFF_P2 as Integer is 24
Constant GQL_OFF_P3 as Integer is 32

Constant GQL_OK as Integer is 0
Constant GQL_NULL as Integer is -1
Constant GQL_PARSE_FAIL as Integer is -2

Constant ASCII_SPACE as Integer is 32
Constant ASCII_TAB as Integer is 9
Constant ASCII_NEWLINE as Integer is 10
Constant ASCII_CR as Integer is 13
Constant ASCII_COMMA as Integer is 44
Constant ASCII_HASH as Integer is 35
Constant ASCII_LBRACE as Integer is 123
Constant ASCII_RBRACE as Integer is 125
Constant ASCII_LBRACKET as Integer is 91
Constant ASCII_RBRACKET as Integer is 93
Constant ASCII_LPAREN as Integer is 40
Constant ASCII_RPAREN as Integer is 41
Constant ASCII_COLON as Integer is 58
Constant ASCII_DOLLAR as Integer is 36
Constant ASCII_AT as Integer is 64
Constant ASCII_QUOTE as Integer is 34
Constant ASCII_BANG as Integer is 33
Constant ASCII_DOT as Integer is 46
Constant ASCII_EQ as Integer is 61
Constant ASCII_DASH as Integer is 45
Constant ASCII_UNDERSCORE as Integer is 95
Constant ASCII_BACKSLASH as Integer is 92

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RECORD ALLOCATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a tagged 40-byte GraphQL record.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate; write five slots.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_alloc" takes kind as Integer, p0 as Integer, p1 as Integer, p2 as Integer, p3 as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rec be proc allocate from Layout with GQL_RECORD_SIZE
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, GQL_OFF_KIND, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, GQL_OFF_P0, p0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, GQL_OFF_P1, p1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, GQL_OFF_P2, p2
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, GQL_OFF_P3, p3
    Return rec
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PUBLIC CONSTRUCTORS - executable document
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a GraphQL operation definition per spec section 2.3.

Payload slots:
  p0 = operation name (optional, 0 if anonymous)
  p1 = selection set (required, non-zero)
  p2 = variable definitions list (or 0)
  p3 = (low byte) op type (GQL_OP_QUERY / MUTATION / SUBSCRIPTION),
        plus pointer-encoded directive list in high bits (the
        constructor stores op_type and a directive list separately
        through a dedicated wrapper - see gql_operation_set_directives).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_OPERATION; encode op_type in p3.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name, selection set, and variable definitions.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_operation" takes op_type as Integer, name as Integer, selection_set as Integer, variables as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rec be proc gql_alloc with GQL_OPERATION, name, selection_set, variables, op_type
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Attach a directives list to an operation.  We store this in the high-bit
indirection via a small 16-byte wrapper that holds (op_type, directives)
so the original p3 slot can keep encoding op_type for fast access.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate a 16-byte wrapper if p3 is not yet a pointer; store op_type at
offset 0 and directives at offset 8.  Replace p3.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns the wrapper and the directives list.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_operation_set_directives" takes operation as Integer, directives as Integer returns Integer:
    If operation is equal to 0:
        Return GQL_NULL
    End If
    Let p3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with operation, GQL_OFF_P3
    Note: If p3 is small (op_type integer 1..3), promote it to a wrapper.
    If p3 is less than 16:
        Let wrap be proc allocate from Layout with 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wrap, 0, p3
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wrap, 8, directives
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with operation, GQL_OFF_P3, wrap
        Return GQL_OK
    End If
    Note: Already a wrapper; just update the directives slot.
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p3, 8, directives
    Return GQL_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the operation type (GQL_OP_QUERY / MUTATION / SUBSCRIPTION) handling
both the in-place small encoding and the wrapper form.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load p3; if small integer, return as-is; else load wrapper offset 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_operation_get_op_type" takes operation as Integer returns Integer:
    If operation is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with operation, GQL_OFF_P3
    If p3 is less than 16:
        Return p3
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p3, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the operation's directives list (0 if none).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load p3; return 0 if small, else wrapper offset 8.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_operation_get_directives" takes operation as Integer returns Integer:
    If operation is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with operation, GQL_OFF_P3
    If p3 is less than 16:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p3, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a selection set per spec section 2.4.  selections is a List of
GQL_FIELD / GQL_FRAGMENT_SPREAD / GQL_INLINE_FRAGMENT records.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_SELECTION_SET.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns the selections list.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_selection_set" takes selections as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_SELECTION_SET, selections, 0, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a field selection per spec section 2.5.

Payload slots:
  p0 = name (required)
  p1 = arguments list (or 0)
  p2 = nested selection set (or 0)
  p3 = (alias_or_0)
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_FIELD.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name, args, nested selection set, and alias.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_field" takes alias as Integer, name as Integer, args as Integer, nested as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_FIELD, name, args, nested, alias
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct an argument record per spec section 2.6.

Payload slots:
  p0 = name
  p1 = value record
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_ARGUMENT.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name and value.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_argument" takes name as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_ARGUMENT, name, value, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a fragment definition per spec section 2.8.

Payload slots:
  p0 = fragment name
  p1 = selection set
  p2 = directives list (or 0)
  p3 = type condition (named type name string)
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_FRAGMENT_DEFINITION.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name, selection set, directives, and type condition.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_fragment_definition" takes name as Integer, type_condition as Integer, selection_set as Integer, directives as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_FRAGMENT_DEFINITION, name, selection_set, directives, type_condition
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a fragment spread per spec section 2.8.1.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_FRAGMENT_SPREAD; p0 = fragment name, p1 = directives.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name and directives.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_fragment_spread" takes name as Integer, directives as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_FRAGMENT_SPREAD, name, directives, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct an inline fragment per spec section 2.8.2.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_INLINE_FRAGMENT; p0 = type condition (or 0),
p1 = selection set, p2 = directives.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns all three.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_inline_fragment" takes type_condition as Integer, selection_set as Integer, directives as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_INLINE_FRAGMENT, type_condition, selection_set, directives, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Variable definition per spec section 2.10.

Payload slots:
  p0 = variable name (no '$' prefix)
  p1 = type record (named / list / non-null)
  p2 = default value (or 0)
  p3 = directives list (or 0)
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_VARIABLE_DEFINITION.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns all four payloads.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_variable_definition" takes name as Integer, type_record as Integer, default_value as Integer, directives as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_VARIABLE_DEFINITION, name, type_record, default_value, directives
End Process

@Reasoning
Variable reference (the '$name' form used inside argument values).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_VARIABLE; p0 = name.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_variable" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_VARIABLE, name, 0, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Directive use per spec section 2.12.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_DIRECTIVE; p0 = name (without '@'), p1 = arguments.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns name and arguments.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_directive" takes name as Integer, args as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_DIRECTIVE, name, args, 0, 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALUE CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Integer value (spec section 2.9.1).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_VALUE_INT.  Stored as text (canonical decimal) since
GraphQL integers can exceed 64 bits in principle.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns text.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_value_int" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_VALUE_INT, text, 0, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
