@Reasoning
Schema definition per spec 3.3.  Maps the query/mutation/subscription
operations to named root types.

Payload slots:
  p0 = query type name
  p1 = mutation type name (or 0)
  p2 = subscription type name (or 0)
  p3 = directives
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
gql_alloc with GQL_SCHEMA_DEFINITION.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owns payloads.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_schema_definition" takes query_type as Integer, mutation_type as Integer, subscription_type as Integer, directives as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc gql_alloc with GQL_SCHEMA_DEFINITION, query_type, mutation_type, subscription_type, directives
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gql_kind" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_KIND
End Process

Process called "gql_p0" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P0
End Process

Process called "gql_p1" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P1
End Process

Process called "gql_p2" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P2
End Process

Process called "gql_p3" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P3
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Recursively destroy a GraphQL AST node and every owned payload.
Dispatch on kind to decide whether each payload is a string, a list, or
an AST subtree.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Switch on kind; recurse on AST payloads; walk lists and recurse; free
string payloads; finally release the record.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(subtree size).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Shared subtrees must NOT be passed.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_destroy" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return GQL_OK
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_KIND
    Let p0 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P0
    Let p1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P1
    Let p2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P2
    Let p3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, GQL_OFF_P3

    If kind is equal to GQL_OPERATION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p1
        If p2 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p2
        End If
        If p3 is greater than or equal to 16:
            Let dirs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p3, 8
            If dirs is not equal to 0:
                proc gql_destroy_list with dirs
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_SELECTION_SET:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_FIELD:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p1
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p2
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_ARGUMENT:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p1
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_FRAGMENT_DEFINITION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p1
        If p2 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p2
        End If
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_FRAGMENT_SPREAD:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p1
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_INLINE_FRAGMENT:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p1
        If p2 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p2
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VARIABLE_DEFINITION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p1
        proc gql_destroy with p2
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VARIABLE:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_DIRECTIVE:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Values.
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_INT:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_FLOAT:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_STRING:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_ENUM:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_VARIABLE:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_LIST:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_VALUE_OBJECT:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p0
        End If
    End If

    Note: Type references.
    If kind is equal to GQL_TYPE_NAMED:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_TYPE_LIST:
        proc gql_destroy with p0
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_TYPE_NON_NULL:
        proc gql_destroy with p0
    End If

    Note: SDL definitions.
    If kind is equal to GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_SCALAR:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p1
        End If
        If p2 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p2
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_TYPE_DEFINITION_OBJECT:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p1
        End If
        If p2 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p2
        End If
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_FIELD_DEFINITION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p1
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p2
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_INPUT_VALUE_DEFINITION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        proc gql_destroy with p1
        proc gql_destroy with p2
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p3
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_ENUM_VALUE_DEFINITION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p1
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to GQL_SCHEMA_DEFINITION:
        If p0 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p0
        End If
        If p1 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p1
        End If
        If p2 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with p2
        End If
        If p3 is not equal to 0:
            proc gql_destroy_list with p3
        End If
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with node
    Return GQL_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: destroy a List of GraphQL AST nodes.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Iterate and recurse via gql_destroy.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(list size).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_destroy_list" takes lst as Integer returns Integer:
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return GQL_OK
    End If
    Let cc be proc list_length from List with lst
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than cc:
        Let e be proc list_get from List with lst, i
        proc gql_destroy with e
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with lst
    Return GQL_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MINIMAL PARSER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Skip whitespace and comments in GraphQL source.  GraphQL whitespace per
spec section 2.1.4 is space, tab, comma, CR, LF; '#' starts a
line-comment.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Linear scan; skip whitespace and comma "tokens", drop comments through
to next newline.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(whitespace + comment length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_skip_ws" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be pos
    While p is less than len:
        Let b be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
        Let advance be 0
        If b is equal to ASCII_SPACE:
            Set advance to 1
        End If
        If b is equal to ASCII_TAB:
            Set advance to 1
        End If
        If b is equal to ASCII_NEWLINE:
            Set advance to 1
        End If
        If b is equal to ASCII_CR:
            Set advance to 1
        End If
        If b is equal to ASCII_COMMA:
            Set advance to 1
        End If
        If b is equal to ASCII_HASH:
            Note: Skip to end of line.  After consuming the LF the outer
            Note: loop will resume classifying the next character.
            Let comment_done be 0
            While comment_done is equal to 0:
                If p is greater than or equal to len:
                    Set comment_done to 1
                End If
                If p is less than len:
                    Let c be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
                    Set p to p plus 1
                    If c is equal to ASCII_NEWLINE:
                        Set comment_done to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End While
            Set advance to 0
        End If
        If advance is equal to 0:
            Set p to len plus 1
        End If
        If advance is equal to 1:
            Set p to p plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If p is greater than len:
        Set p to p minus 1
    End If
    Return p
End Process

@Reasoning
Test whether a byte is a GraphQL Name start character (letter or '_'),
per spec section 2.1.9.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
ASCII range checks.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
None.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_is_name_start" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to ASCII_UNDERSCORE:
        Return 1
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 65:
        If b is less than or equal to 90:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 97:
        If b is less than or equal to 122:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Test whether a byte is a GraphQL Name continue character (Name start +
digit), per spec section 2.1.9.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Name start plus digits.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
None.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_is_name_continue" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let s be proc gql_is_name_start with b
    If s is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 48:
        If b is less than or equal to 57:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read a GraphQL Name starting at pos.  Returns end offset; caller
substrings the [pos, end) range.  Returns pos on failure.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Linear scan.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(name length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_read_name_end" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer returns Integer:
    If pos is greater than or equal to len:
        Return pos
    End If
    Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, pos
    Let ok be proc gql_is_name_start with first
    If ok is equal to 0:
        Return pos
    End If
    Let p be pos plus 1
    While p is less than len:
        Let b be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
        Let cont be proc gql_is_name_continue with b
        If cont is equal to 0:
            Return p
        End If
        Set p to p plus 1
    End While
    Return p
End Process

@Reasoning
Compare the substring text[pos..pos+len_of_keyword) to a keyword string.
Returns 1 on match, 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Byte-by-byte compare.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(keyword length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_text_equals_keyword" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, end_pos as Integer, keyword as Integer returns Integer:
    Let span_len be end_pos minus pos
    Let kw_len be proc string_length from StringCore with keyword
    If span_len is not equal to kw_len:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than kw_len:
        Let a be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, pos plus i
        Let b be proc string_char_at from StringCore with keyword, i
        If a is not equal to b:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a minimal GraphQL executable document: a single operation
definition or a shorthand query "{ field1 field2 }".  Returns a List of
top-level definitions (currently just one operation) on success, or 0
on parse failure.

This parser intentionally implements the most-common subset needed for
client query roundtripping: shorthand query, named operations,
selection sets with nested selections, simple field names (no
arguments / aliases / directives in this minimal pass).  The full SDL
parser is not in this minimal scope; it is intentionally TODO for the
follow-up sprint and is documented as such in the report.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Skip leading whitespace.  If next non-ws character is '{', parse a
shorthand query.  If the next token is the keyword 'query', 'mutation',
or 'subscription', parse a named operation: keyword name? {...}.  Build
the AST via the constructors above.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(N) in source bytes.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on failure.  Partial trees are leaked on failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "graphql_parse" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let p be proc gql_skip_ws with source, 0, len
    If p is greater than or equal to len:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, p
    Let op_type be GQL_OP_QUERY
    Let op_name be 0
    Let advance_start be p
    If first is equal to ASCII_LBRACE:
        Note: Shorthand query.
        Set advance_start to p
    End If
    If first is not equal to ASCII_LBRACE:
        Let name_end be proc gql_read_name_end with source, p, len
        If name_end is equal to p:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let is_query be proc gql_text_equals_keyword with source, p, name_end, "query"
        Let is_mut be proc gql_text_equals_keyword with source, p, name_end, "mutation"
        Let is_sub be proc gql_text_equals_keyword with source, p, name_end, "subscription"
        Let any_op_kw be 0
        If is_query is equal to 1:
            Set op_type to GQL_OP_QUERY
            Set any_op_kw to 1
        End If
        If is_mut is equal to 1:
            Set op_type to GQL_OP_MUTATION
            Set any_op_kw to 1
        End If
        If is_sub is equal to 1:
            Set op_type to GQL_OP_SUBSCRIPTION
            Set any_op_kw to 1
        End If
        If any_op_kw is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set p to name_end
        Set p to (proc gql_skip_ws with source, p, len)
        If p is less than len:
            Let nb be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, p
            Let is_name_start be proc gql_is_name_start with nb
            If is_name_start is equal to 1:
                Let nm_end be proc gql_read_name_end with source, p, len
                Set op_name to (proc string_substring from StringPrim with source, p, nm_end minus p)
                Set p to nm_end
                Set p to (proc gql_skip_ws with source, p, len)
            End If
        End If
        If p is greater than or equal to len:
            If op_name is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with op_name
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Let lb be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, p
        If lb is not equal to ASCII_LBRACE:
            If op_name is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with op_name
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Set advance_start to p
    End If

    Let selection_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with selection_slot, 0, 0
    Let after_sel be proc gql_parse_selection_set with source, advance_start, len, selection_slot
    Let sel_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with selection_slot, 0
    proc deallocate from Layout with selection_slot
    If after_sel is less than 0:
        If op_name is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with op_name
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let op_node be proc gql_operation with op_type, op_name, sel_set, 0
    Let definitions be proc list_create from List
    proc list_push from List with definitions, op_node
    Return definitions
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a selection set '{...}' starting at the '{' at offset pos.  Writes
the resulting GQL_SELECTION_SET pointer into out_slot and returns the
offset just past '}', or -1 on parse error.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Confirm '{'.  Loop reading Names (each becomes a field with no args).
If the next non-ws character is '{', recursively parse a nested
selection set and attach it as the field's nested set.  End on '}'.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(input length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
None.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "gql_parse_selection_set" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer, out_slot as Integer returns Integer:
    If pos is greater than or equal to len:
        Return -1
    End If
    Let lb be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, pos
    If lb is not equal to ASCII_LBRACE:
        Return -1
    End If
    Let p be pos plus 1
    Let selections be proc list_create from List
    Let keep_going be 1
    While keep_going is equal to 1:
        Set p to (proc gql_skip_ws with text, p, len)
        If p is greater than or equal to len:
            Note: unterminated.
            Set keep_going to 0
            proc gql_destroy_list with selections
            Return -1
        End If
        Let b be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
        If b is equal to ASCII_RBRACE:
            Set keep_going to 0
            Set p to p plus 1
        End If
        If b is not equal to ASCII_RBRACE:
            Let is_start be proc gql_is_name_start with b
            If is_start is equal to 0:
                Set keep_going to 0
                proc gql_destroy_list with selections
                Return -1
            End If
            If is_start is equal to 1:
                Let name_end be proc gql_read_name_end with text, p, len
                Let name_dup be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, p, name_end minus p
                Let nested be 0
                Set p to name_end
                Set p to (proc gql_skip_ws with text, p, len)
                If p is less than len:
                    Let nb be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
                    If nb is equal to ASCII_LBRACE:
                        Let nslot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nslot, 0, 0
                        Let after_n be proc gql_parse_selection_set with text, p, len, nslot
                        Set nested to (proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with nslot, 0)
                        proc deallocate from Layout with nslot
                        If after_n is less than 0:
                            proc deallocate from Layout with name_dup
                            proc gql_destroy_list with selections
                            Return -1
                        End If
                        Set p to after_n
                    End If
                End If
                Let field_node be proc gql_field with 0, name_dup, 0, nested
                proc list_push from List with selections, field_node
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let sel_set be proc gql_selection_set with selections
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_slot, 0, sel_set
    Return p
End Process

Note: Serializer is provided in a separate module to keep this file focused on
Note: AST construction, destruction, and parsing.  See query/graphql_serializer.runa
Note: (forthcoming) for the round-trip text emitter; for now callers wishing to
Note: serialize an AST should walk it using the gql_kind / gql_p0..p3 accessors
Note: and emit text themselves.  The AST itself is the source of truth.
